column5: Just wondering if there are any new foods etc that arent being allowed when crossing into Canada this year thanks

Read a post or two that eggs from Indiana and a few other states are still prohibited. Wish I could remember those other states. Our group eats a lot of eggs for breakfasts so I make sure the eggs don't come from Indiana. Same with uncooked chicken breasts.
We just purchased our eggs in International falls & Kept the receipt in case they asked. They didnt.
